title: Kentucky QB commit gets offer from Tennessee
text:
Manage Kentucky QB commit gets offer from Tennessee A three-star quarterback from Lawrenceville, Ga., who has been committed to Kentucky for months says he received an offer from Tennessee on Saturday. 
Three-star junior quarterback Jarren Williams of Central Gwinnett High School in Lawrenceville, Ga., a Kentucky commitment, posted Saturday on his Twitter account that he received a scholarship offer from Tennessee. 
" Honored and (privileged) to (receive) an offer from The University of Tennessee!!" he tweeted. (What's next for the Vols? Make sure you're in the loop â€” take five seconds to sign up for our FREE Vols newsletter now!) 
The 6-foot-3, 201-pound Williams, who has been committed to the Wildcats since June, holds offers from more than a dozen schools, including Florida State, Miami, Mississippi State, Missouri, South Carolina, Houston, Louisville, Maryland and West Virginia. 
Williams is ranked the nation's No. 472 overall prospect and No. 18 dual-threat quarterback in the 247Sports Composite for the 2018 class. He's also ranked by 247Sports as the nation's No. 334 overall prospect and No. 16 dual-threat quarterback.
